==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Demitint
<hw>Dem"i*tint`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Fine Arts)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>That part of a painting, engraving, or the like, which
is neither in full darkness nor full light.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The
shade itself; neither the darkest nor the lightest in a composition.
Also called <xex>half tint</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Demitone</ent>⟦br⟧
